# Running a python environment on Laguna using Conda

## LogIn to CARC OnDemand

1. Go to laguna-ood.carc.usc.edu in your browser
2. Log in with your CGU credentials
3. From the top menu, click Interactive Apps → JupyterLab

## Configure the Session — Critical Settings

JupyterLab version
Partition
Number of CPUs
GPU model
Number of GPUs
Wall time

Click launch, the sessions is queued

## Setup a Conda environment

On the Jupyter Lab session, load a terminal

type the commands

```
$ module load conda
$ conda create -n qcl_bootcamp python=3.12 -y
$ conda activate qcl_bootcamp
```

Install libraries


```
$ pip install numpy pandas matplotlib ipykernel
$ python -m ipykernel install --user --name qcl_bootcamp --display-name "QCL Bootcamp Env"
```

## Select the kernel in your notebook
At the top-right corner of the notebook select your kernel
